article.headline: Radford 69, Liberty 54
article.story: RADFORD, Va. (AP) -- Whit Holcomb-Faye scored 15 of his 36 points from the free throw line as Radford beat Liberty 69-54 on Saturday. Holcomb-Faye was 15-of-17 from the charity stripe and shot 5-of-11 from beyond the arch. Radford (15-11, 8-6 Big South Conference) hit 25 of 27 from the free throw line in the second half and 86.5 percent for the game off 32-of-37 shooting. Reggie McIntyre added 19 points and 12 rebounds for Radford. Larry Blair led Liberty (6-20, 2-11) with 21 points. Anthony Smith had 13 and Eric Bigby added 10.
